{{Infobox language family |name=Baining |altname=East New Britain |region=[[New Britain]] |ethnicity=[[Baining people]] |familycolor=Papuan |family = One of the world's primary [[language family|language families]] |child1=Baining |child2=Taulil |glotto=none |glotto2=bain1263 |glottoname2={{nowrap|Baining proper}} |glotto3=taul1250 |glottoname3=Taulil–Butam }}
The '''Baining''' or '''East New Britain languages''' are a possible small [[language family]] spoken by the [[Baining people]] on the island of [[New Britain]] in [[Papua New Guinea]]. They were classified as [[East Papuan languages]] by Wurm, but this does not now seem tenable.
The languages are: *Baining proper: [[Mali language|Mali]], [[Qaqet language|Qaqet]], [[Kairak language|Kairak]], [[Simbali language|Simbali]], [[Ura language (Papua New Guinea)|Ura]], ?[[Makolkol language|Makolkol]] (extinct?) *Taulil: [[Taulil language|Taulil]], [[Butam language|Butam]] (extinct)
''Glottolog'' does not accept that a connection between the two branches has been demonstrated.<ref name="Glottolog2" />
==Pronouns==
The pronouns Ross reconstructs for proto-Baining are,
:{| class=wikitable |- | '''I''' || ''*ŋa'' || '''we two''' || ''*(ŋ)un'' || '''we''' || ''*udu'' |- | '''thou''' || ''*ŋi'' || '''you two''' || ''*yu'' || '''you''' || ''*ŋan'' |- | '''he''' || ''*(k)a'' || '''they two (M)''' || ''*ip'' || rowspan=2|'''they''' || rowspan=2|''*ta'' |- | '''she''' || ''*(k)e'' || '''they two (F)''' || ? |}
The possessive pronouns ''his'' and ''her'' are ''*vat'' and ''*vet.''
