'''Halife Altay''' (1917–2003) was a [[Kazakh language|Kazakh]] author and anthropologist. He fled the [[People's Republic of China]] during the [[Kazakh exodus from Xinjiang]], and later wrote about the migration and about Kazakh culture. He lived in [[Turkey]] for a period, and then moved to [[Kazakhstan]].
==Works== *''Halife Altay, Anayurttan Anadoluʹya, Ankara: Kültür Bakanlığı (1981). (Turkish)'' *''Halife Altay, Kazak Türklerine aid şecere, Istanbul (1997) (Turkish)''
