{{Infobox language |name=Mursi |nativename= |pronunciation= |states=[[Ethiopia]] |region=Central [[Omo River (Ethiopia)|Omo]] |ethnicity=[[Mursi people|Mursi]] |speakers={{sigfig|7390|2}} |date=2007 census |ref=<ref>[http://www.csa.gov.et/index.php?option=com_rubberdoc&view=doc&id=264&format=raw&Itemid=521 Ethiopia 2007 Census]</ref> |familycolor=Nilo-Saharan |fam2=[[Eastern Sudanic]] |fam3=[[Kir–Abbaian languages|Kir–Abbaian]] |fam4=[[Surmic languages|Surmic]] |fam5=South |fam6=Southeast |fam7=Suri–Mursi |iso3=muz |glotto=murs1242 |glottorefname=Mursi |script=Ethiopic }}
'''Mursi''' (also Dama, Merdu, Meritu, Murzi, Murzu) is a [[Nilo-Saharan languages|Nilo-Saharan]] [[Eastern Sudanic languages|Eastern Sudanic]] language spoken by the [[Mursi people]], in the central [[Omo River (Ethiopia)|Omo]] region of southwest [[Ethiopia]]. It is similar to [[Suri language|Suri]], spoken in most of the immediately surrounding area.
